==English==

===Etymology===
<!--Derived meaning during WWII when such images were "pinned" to a surface (eg: locker) or otherwise displayed and made popular, ie: on bomber nose fairings.-->
From mechanic's practice of pinning up the centerfolds on the notice board or wall of a predomanently male-only area; a [[garage]].

===Noun===
'''pinup'''

# A [[pinup girl]]; a [[portrait]] or representation of a provocative model or [[centerfold]].